replyContent: Hey there, thank you for your review, we apologize for this inconvenience. Because Stamina mode is for battery preservation, devices with this feature enabled allow for incoming calls, messages and some notifications. Anything additional has a change of compromised performance. Please reach out with questions to support@brainiumstudios.com

This review is based solely on the expert level. I love to play sudoku at expert level, but didn't really care for it on this app. It is not like traditional expert levels where you can solve 1/3 to 1/2 of the puzzle using intermediate strategies, then you need expert/ advanced techniques to solve the puzzle. This app heavily relies on 2 strategies. The finned swordfish and linking. I have only seen two other strategies used, which were the finned x-wing and trial-and-error (if you even consider that a strategy). I do like the layout, the hint options, and the statistics though. But if you're looking to mainly play on the expert level and have played on the expert level before, I do not suggest this app.

I tried several Sudoku apps on the android market place. This is by far the most feature rich, well built, and intuitive Sudoku app there is. There are so many useful features in this game and you can toggle each of them on and off. For example, if you make notes, you can set it to auto clear the notes of numbers you've filled it instead of erasing them yourself.   Other useful features are things like checking to see what numbers are wrong, using the hint system to alert you to where you should be looking, or going one step further and using the hint system to teach you advanced techniques to figure out the numbers on harder puzzles.   I can't think of anything I would change or add to this app other than a few more unique themes. Not a huge fan of the bamboo style but who really cares.   TLDR: if you're wanting the best Sudoku app, legit, stop right here. This is it.

replyContent:
Hi Andre-

We responded to your email the next business day- you emailed Friday and we responded on Monday. Like most businesses we are out of the office on weekends :) 

We provided solutions that generally fix most issues, and were unaware at the time that the issue was caused by a bug. Glad to hear the update helped!
